Title: GOD OF WAR 4 Trailer #2 (2018)
Comment: Can tell that ...Kratos as been a huge source of inspiration while being young ... got a ruff childhood, always switching school to finish in a house fill with evil ... I was 13 maybe, when the first one came on ps2. I was really excited to play it every day. And I always admire the will to keep going of Kratos. Even witrh all that he pass through, he keep focus on his goal. I almost see myself as Kratos by the time, but today im really more mature, still got some angryness sometimes that I got hard time to control because of my past, I always feel the need to testy myself and to defend the weak (yeah thats not a Kratos fact ;) ). And im not big and muscular, but I aint fear pain or death. My real problem today is the way I build my ''shell''. And the hate that fuel me from all my childhood. It hard to get rid of it ... and even in that new God of War, I really feel myself as Kratos feel, with my 2 kids (2 boys 5 and 7) and my will to be the best father while making mistake here and there but still really peaceful over my childs and I want them to become great men and to do great deeds. Even with all what Kratos did, all his anger and all his sins he do what he have to do and he never step back. I can tell that Kratos ''help'' me to pass my childhood and to make me do huuuuge choice. Today I feel powerful like never before. And not because im strong (im not weak by the way ;) ) but because my mental is, im fearless over tuff times and tuff choice but I dont ever quit trying to succeed. Thx to you Kratos ... and thx to you Sony you are pillar to what I am today ! And whoever will tell (haha, you got power from video game you geek) ... yes I do, and im really prood and lucky to become who I am from it !

Title: GOD OF WAR 4 Trailer #2 (2018)
Comment: Omfg dude, no thanks. We already have Last of Us and Horizon Zero Dawn, and trying to turn GoW into a bastardized, oscar-bait fusion of the two isn't what GoW is about. An old and grizzled, no-blades-of-chaos-having, pretending-like-i-can-be-a-father-now Kratos who doesn't even have the original voice actor anymore is just not appealing in my eyes. The Kratos I know and love would've chopped this kid into ground beef and used his remains as a key or something the instant he said some shit like "daddy?". But I can't wait for the explanation of how this motherfucker is STILL alive, much less the entire planet after he KILLED ALL OF THE GODS. Suspension of disbelief is one thing - and GoW was already pushing it to begin with, but made up for it with some damn fine turn-brain-off-and-enjoy combat - but asking me to seal it in a coffin and launch it into space is just not gonna happen.

Title: GOD OF WAR 4 Trailer #2 (2018)
Comment:
really, now? I can accept him slaughtering most of the Olympians - they were morally dubious at best. (A few exceptions there... For example, I really think you did Hades a disservice - in myth, he's quite a nice guy. I mean, yes, sure, he kidnaps his wife. But besides that, he NEVER cheats on her, he's fair in his treatment of mortal souls that arrive downstairs, and has a generally loving and equal relationship with Persephone, something you guys really misrepresented too. And as another example, Gaia really didn't deserve to die. And he should've tried to actually /save/ Prometheus - Prometheus is the ultimate tragic hero of Greek myth. Really, his whole death-and-destruction thing is somewhat unjustifiable. If I were him, I'd have instead formed an alliance with, say, Hades, Prometheus, Gaia, perhaps a few other titans and deities such as Helios, Hermes or Athena... And then worked towards dethroning Zeus, because Zeus's a tyrant of the worst kind. For the sake of mankind, not personal vengeance)

But... I'm getting sidetracked. My point was, originally: REALLY?! What did he Norse gods ever do wrong damnit!
Odin is incredible! He's wise, has an awesome sense of style, has bloody AWESOME ravens (Huginn & Muninn), has rune magic for which he actually worked /hard/, being stuck on a spear to a goddamn tree for DAYS, and sacrificed one of his eyes at the roots of Yggdrasil (I fear Yggdrasil's going to burn in this next part...)

... And you're gonna have Kratos kill him? For what crime exactly? HASNT KRATOS CAUSED ENOUGH DAMAGE?!

LEAVE ASGARD ALONE! LEAVE VANAHEIM ALONE TOO!  AND LOKI! SPARE LOKI TOO, LOKI IS AWESOME AS WELL! PLEASE?! JUST LET THEM RAGNAROK IN PEACE (And yes, I know that's a self-contradicting statement. I CARE NOT! FOR THE NOIRSE!)


Also... What's next? Him going on a rampage in Egypt too? And then Japan, or the Aztec pantheon? Oh, perhaps him destroying all of Africa while he's at it? How about all of Asia, from India through Vietnam to Indonesia, and then backtracking to China, and then Japan? And then maybe go and challenge the Lovecraftian gods too, killing all of them? And oh, oh, I forgot the Incans, those deities must die too.

WHEN WILL THIS RAMPAGE END!??!?!?!
